article.headline: Morgan St. 58, Md.-Eastern Shore 45
article.story: BALTIMORE -- Shaquille Duncan scored 17 points and Morgan State opened the second half with an 18-2 run en route to a 58-45 victory over Maryland-Eastern Shore in a Mid-Eastern Athletic Association game on Saturday. DeWayne Jackson chipped in with 15 points and seven rebounds for the Bears (12-14, 8-6), who have won six of their past seven games. Troy Snyder had 16 points and seven rebounds and Kevin Mays added 12 points for the Hawks (2-23, 2-12), who have 10 of the past 11 games. It was close at halftime- Morgan State led 20-19 -- as both teams shot badly. Morgan State was 7 of 27 from the field, and UMES was 6 of 22. The Bears shot 55.2 percent in the second half (16 of 29), the Hawks 34.5 percent (10 of 29). Morgan State outscored Maryland-Eastern Shore 34-18 in the paint and 12-2 off turnovers.
